---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="Submit — Pixel Noise" description="Submit your work, tools, or articles to be featured on Pixel Noise.">

  <div class="page-header">
    <h1>Submit</h1>
  </div>

  <div class="container">
    <div class="content-page-body" style="padding: 0;">
      <p>Pixel Noise welcomes submissions from designers, studios, brands, and emerging creatives who want to be featured. Whether it's a project you're proud of, a tool you've built, a brand you've developed, or an article you'd like to contribute — we want to hear from you.</p>
      <p>Due to the volume of submissions we receive, we're not able to respond to every message. But we review every submission carefully to ensure the content is relevant and of high quality. If we decide to feature your work or need more information, we will contact you directly.</p>
      <p>To submit, send your materials to <a href="mailto:hello@pixelnoise.dev" style="color: var(--color-accent); text-decoration: underline;">hello@pixelnoise.dev</a> with the subject line "Submission — [Your Name / Studio Name]".</p>

      <p><strong>Please include:</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>Your full name and a short bio</li>
        <li>Your portfolio or website URL</li>
        <li>A description of the work, tool, brand, or article you're submitting</li>
        <li>A brief introduction about you or your company</li>
        <li>At least 5–10 JPEG or PNG image files (via Dropbox or similar file-sharing service)</li>
        <li>Full credits if the project involved multiple collaborators</li>
        <li>Press releases are welcome and encouraged</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Affiliate & Sponsored Content</h2>
      <p>Pixel Noise is open to affiliate partnerships and sponsored content opportunities. If your submission includes a commercial arrangement or affiliate relationship, please note this clearly in your message. We maintain full editorial discretion over how all content is presented on the site.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</Base>
